description: Combined into one, double-sized colossal issue, Nexus #101 and #102 will together bring the series to its final conclusion. Kreed, the most lethal Quatro of all time, has returned - but how? Elvon Supreme leads the greatest fleet ever launched on Ylum. Nexus travels to Earth to address the United Planets. Ylum stands isolated and condemned by the United Web as the greatest invasion force in history draws near. Sundra defends her child from a merciless foe, a foe who was once Sundra's best friend. Finally, Nexus must choose between saving his planet and suffering universal condemnation or obey the will of the web!
name: Space Opera The Conclusion

description:
Korak's adventures at DC continue, and he's got to deal with some troublemakers called The Nazis!

Meanwhile, Carson Napier is on Venus, and there's still a failure to communicate!
name: The War Machine!; The Girl In The Garden

description:
Revealed at last in his own title - the origins of Korak!

Meanwhile, Carson is settling into life on Venus. He's even courting a nice young girl... unfortunately, she's also a princess!
name: The Search;Gathering Tarel

description:
Korak reaches his 50th issue, but there's not much to celebrate - he still has to find Meriem!

Back on Venus, Carson gets the shock of his life!
name: Underworld;By Kamlot's Grave!

description:
Korak is reunited with Meriem... only trouble is, their reunion is on a chain gang underneath a volcano!

Back on Venus, Carson's been taken prisoner by the Thorists... poor Thorists!
name: Into The Depths!;Mutiny At Sea

description:
Korak's search for Meriem cannot be halted... except perhaps by a homicidal cyclops!

Back on Venus, Carson is now a pirate captain!
name: The Outcasts;Duare... Princess of Venus

description:
Korak's still looking for Meriem, but all he's finding is trouble!

Back on Venus, Carson's finding that romancing a princess is a lot like being a pirate captain - they're both pretty difficult work!
name: The Tribe That Time Forgot!;Catastrophe

description:
Korak's quest for Meriem is delayed by a few trifling matters... just some ferocious beasts and being made to battle his best friend for the right to rule a tribe, that's all!

Back on Venus, Carson has to face The Seven Doors!
name: Blood Brothers;Into The Land of Noobol

description:
Korak's search for Meriem is halted yet again, this time by some slavers, who want to turn him into some merchandise! Man, did they pick the wrong boy!

Back on Venus, Carson Napier is reunited with an old friend... and an old enemy!
name: Terror Mountain;Lost On Venus

description:
Korak has found Meriem again... but is his search truly over?

Back on Venus, Carson and Duare are together again... lost in Thorist territory!
name: The Mound of Skulls!; Babes In The Woods
